definition.value: A D-galactosylglycerol that is alpha-D-glucofuranose in which the hydrogen of the anomeric hydroxy group has been replaced by a 2,3-dihydroxypropyl group.
An amino disaccharide that is D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been converted into the corresponding 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranosyl derivative.
An amino disaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose and-beta-D-glucopyranuronic acid residues joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
